OL,3,CMan in custody after arrest on
OL,4,Csuspicion of murdering Ann Widdecombe
OL,6,FIn a video statement published on
OL,7,Fsocial media, he added: "And I do fear
OL,8,Fthat for anybody in public life, or
OL,9,Fespecially the political space, things
OL,10,Fhave become even more dangerous today."
OL,12,FMeanwhile, Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,13,FStarmer urged people to come together
OL,14,Facross political divides following the
OL,15,Fmurder.
OL,17,FHe said he had spoken to his likely
OL,18,Fsuccessor Andy Burnham, Tory leader
OL,19,FKemi Badenoch and Reform UK's Mr
OL,20,FFarage to "urge everybody to come
OL,21,Ftogether at a moment like this".
